x4freetext: -NEUTRON ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING FROM N-14
EN VAN DE GRAAFF TANDEM, PULSED AT A REPETITION
RATE OF 2.5 MHZ, GIVING DEUTERON PULSE LENGTHS OF 1.2
- 0.8 NS FOR DEUTERON ENERGIES OF 4.75 - 10.68 MEV,
RESPECTIVELY. AVERAGE BEAM CURRENTS WERE IN THE INTER-
TARGET CELL OF LENGTH 3.0 CM FILLED WITH DEU-
TERIUM GAS TO A PRESSURE OF 1 KG/CM2. THE TOTAL ENERGY
SPREAD WERE 130 - 80 KEV FOR NEUTRON ENERGIES OF 7.67
SIX IDENTICAL 12.5 CM DIAMETER BY 5 CM THICK
NE 213 LIQUID SCINTILLATORS, MOUNTED ON PHOTOMULTI-
PLIER TUBES XP 1041, WERE USED TO MEASURE THE ANGULAR
DISTRIBUTIONS OF SCATTERED NEUTRONS. THE DETECTORS
WERE SEPARATED BY 20 DEGREES IN THE AZIMUTHAL PLANE.
A SYSTEM OF COLLIMATORS AND SHADOW BARS WERE USED TO
THE RELATIVE NEUTRON FLUX WAS DETERMINED USING
A NEUTRON MONITOR IDENTICAL TO THE DETECTORS
DESCRIBED. IT WAS POSITIONED AT AN ANGLE OF 55
.ABSOLUTE CROSS SECTIONS WERE DETERMINED BY MEASURING
THE NEUTRON FLUX AT 0 DEGREES USING THE SAME DETECTORS
AS FOR MEASURING THE SCATTERED YIELD.
.THE SAMPLE CONSISTED OF LIQUID NITROGEN, CONTAINED IN
A CAN WITH A DIAMETER OF 2.5 CM, A HEIGHT OF 5.2 CM
AND A WALL THICKNESS OF 0.4 MM. THE NITROGEN CONTENT
WAS 0.35E+23 ATOMS/CM3. AN IDENTICAL EMPTY CAN WAS
.CORRECTIONS WERE APPLIED FOR THE VARIATION OF THE
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY WITH ENERGY, ANISOTROPY OF THE
NEUTRONS FROM THE D-D REACTION, FINITE SCATTERING
GEOMETRY, FLUX ATTENUATION, MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND
